[ROLE declarer][STAGE auction-end]
You declare four spades. Count your losers: you have heart losers in hand opposite dummy's singleton \H2. Plan to ruff a heart in dummy before drawing trumps.
[ROLE declarer][STAGE pre-lead]
Before you play to trick one, fix the order in your mind: win the opening lead, lead a heart and ruff it in dummy, and only then start pulling trumps. The ruff must come first.
[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-lead]
West cashes the \CA — looks like the ace from a long club suit, taking a look before committing. That side-suit lead leaves your trumps untouched, so your plan is intact: take the trick, then lead a low heart toward dummy's singleton and ruff it. That ruff disposes of one of your heart losers while dummy still has trumps to do it. Now draw trumps and claim — ten tricks are there.
